# remove glyhb because it can not be used in prediction
dbt <- subset(dbt, select= -c(glyhb))

# remove id because it can not be used in prediction
dbt <- subset(dbt, select= -c(id))

# remove time.ppn because it refers to when a lab was drawn which is not a likely predictor for if someone has a chronic condition. This variable is important for blood glucose monitoring.
dbt <- subset(dbt, select= -c(time.ppn))

# remove location because it can not be used to apply to a broader population
dbt <- subset(dbt, select= -c(location))

#correct frame not being read as factor
dbt$frame <- as.factor(as.character(dbt$frame))

#correct gender not being read as factor
dbt$gender <- as.factor(as.character(dbt$gender))

Step 3 Assess Model Fit

Assess Model assumtions

plot Loess plots

##Loess for chol
dbt$diagnosis <- as.numeric(as.character(dbt$diagnosis))
#Obtain y_bar, smoothed responses using the loess function
y_smooth <- predict(loess(as.numeric(diagnosis) ~chol, data = dbt))
#Which values of y_bar are less than zero or greater than one?
zero_one <- which(y_smooth>0 & y_smooth<1)
#Make plot of X, y_bar for observations with y_bar in (0,1)
plot(jitter(dbt$chol)[zero_one], log(y_smooth[zero_one]/(1-y_smooth[zero_one])))

Above we see close to linear. Chol does not need to be modified with a spline.

##Loess for stab.glu
#Obtain y_bar, smoothed responses using the loess function
y_smooth <- predict(loess(diagnosis ~stab.glu , data = dbt))
#Which values of y_bar are less than zero or greater than one?

##function to create splines, x is predictor, k is vector of knots. Can only do k=3 knots
my.4splines <- function(x,k){
  k1 <- k[1]
  k2 <- k[2]
  k3 <- k[3]
  x.l1 <- NULL
  x.l2 <- NULL
  x.l3 <- NULL
  x.l4 <- NULL
  for (i in 1:length(x)){
    x.l1[i] <- min(x[i],k1)
    x.l2[i] <- max(min(x[i],k2),k1)-k1
    x.l3[i] <- max(min(x[i],k3),k2)-k2
    x.l4[i] <- max(x[i],k3)-k3
  }
  x.s <- cbind(x.l1,x.l2,x.l3,x.l4)
}
#Find knots for age and stab.glu
knots_age <- quantile(dbt$age,c(.10,.50,.90))
knots_stab.glu <- quantile(dbt$stab.glu,c(.10,.50,.90))
#Create splines for age and bmi
age_spline <- my.4splines(dbt$age,knots_age) 
stab.glu_spline <- my.4splines(dbt$stab.glu,knots_stab.glu) 


#Put both sets of splines in a model
reduced2 <- glm(diagnosis~age_spline  +stab.glu_spline + waist + chol ,data=dbt,family=binomial)
